ncy, though the extent of recovery can vary depending on the severity and duration of the condition.\",4\r\n2071,VITAMIN B1 DEFICIENCY,\"A condition caused by insufficient levels of vitamin B1, often resulting from alcohol abuse and leading to Korsakov's syndrome\",2\r\n1074,MENTAL RETARDATION,\"MENTAL RETARDATION, also known as intellectual disability, is a condition characterized by impaired cognitive and social functioning. It is typically diagnosed in individuals under 18 years of age who exhibit an IQ below 70 and demonstrate difficulties in social adaptive abilities. The condition arises from hindered brain development during the perinatal or infant period, which affects overall intellectual and adaptive functioning. MENTAL RETARDATION is classified into four levels—mild, moderate, severe, and profound—based on the individual's IQ score and the extent of their impairments. This condition impacts various aspects of life, including learning, communication, and daily living skills, requiring tailored support and interventions to enhance the individual's quality of life.\",4\r\n1076,WEIS INTELLIGENCE TEST,\"An intelligence test used to diagnose mental retardation, with an IQ below 70 being one of the diagnostic criteria\",1\r\n1075,CHILDREN'S SOCIAL ABILITY RATING SCALE,\"A scale applicable to children aged 6 months to 15 years, used to assess children's social life abilities\",1\r\n1632,DEMENTIA,\"Dementia is a condition involving severe cognitive decline due to brain damage, affecting memory, reasoning, and daily functioning\",3\r\n1633,KORSAKOFF SYNDROME,,2\r\n2069,AMNESTIC SYNDROME,\"A syndrome primarily characterized by severe memory impairment, often caused by vitamin B1 deficiency, hypoxia, or brain injury\",1\r\n424,AFFECTIVE DISORDERS,Affective disorders are mental disorders studied in neuropathology research,1\r\n960,WEIGHT LOSS DRUGS,\"Weight loss drugs, including appetite suppressants and metabolic accelerators, can cause psychiatric symptoms ranging f